Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.08,0:58:22.84,English,,0,0,0,,all you have to do is obey and the world will be perfect.\N{\rChinese}OK?…
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.16,0:58:25.52,English,,0,0,0,,We have come to the end of history.\N{\rChinese}我们已到达历史终点。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.96,0:58:29.02,English,,0,0,0,,History has stopped. Because we have found perfection.\N{\rChinese}历史已停歇，因我们已得以完工。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.50,0:58:34.14,English,,0,0,0,,We have found the perfect model to organize human civilization.\N{\rChinese}我们已找到组织人类文明的完美模型
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.02,0:58:37.02,English,,0,0,0,,We are the perfection. We are the end.\N{\rChinese}我们已在此处……??
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.92,0:58:45.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And so, this is the idea of Roman eternity.\N{\rChinese}...??
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.94,0:58:52.88,English,,0,0,0,,And this marks a radical transition in Western civilization.\N{\rChinese}And ... ...…
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.18,0:58:56.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}...…
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.10,0:59:13.66,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions? One last point is this. Okay?\N{\rChinese}...…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.10,0:59:17.94,English,,0,0,0,,The Romans were like the most non -creative people in the world.\N{\rChinese}罗马人像世界上最不具创意的人一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.00,0:59:21.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They were anti -creative. So, everything that they had, they sold them somewhere else.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们是反创意的。于是，大家都把它们放在别处。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.78,0:59:24.58,English,,0,0,0,,Somewhere else. Okay? So, the question then is.\N{\rChinese}某处…好吧，……
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.58,0:59:27.08,English,,0,0,0,,Where do they get the idea of eternity from?\N{\rChinese}哪里能得到永远的想法？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.80,0:59:32.80,English,,0,0,0,,Can you guess? Egypt.\N{\rChinese}可以说是从埃及的那点儿吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.56,0:59:36.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Next class I will show you\N{\rChinese}好的，下一节课…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.26,0:59:40.78,English,,0,0,0,,that the Romans are using the Egyptian sense of eternity.\N{\rChinese}罗马人正在使用埃及的永远观念。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.98,0:59:49.30,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Okay.\N{\rChinese}好的？ 先回到…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.86,0:59:53.96,English,,0,0,0,,So, I know this is a lot to take in.\N{\rChinese}我知道这很大…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.00,0:59:58.76,English,,0,0,0,,But I want to give you a little bit of a summary. So, feel free to ask some clarification on any point.\N{\rChinese}但我想给你们一点总结。你们可以随时问我任何问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.90,1:00:03.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Are you okay with this?\N{\rChinese}好的？ 这点儿…？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.90,1:00:08.22,English,,0,0,0,,Yes. I still have one question.\N{\rChinese}是的，继续…
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.50,1:00:10.98,English,,0,0,0,,Sure. Is that\N{\rChinese}好的。那是罗马人否定希腓文化吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.98,1:00:15.26,English,,0,0,0,,the Romans rejected the Greek culture?\N{\rChinese}嗯，奥古斯都·凯撒想要他们去掉希腓文化。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.54,1:00:18.92,English,,0,0,0,,Well, Augustus Caesar wants them to reject Greek culture.\N{\rChinese}Well, Augustus Caesar wantsthem to reject Greek culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.10,1:00:21.66,English,,0,0,0,,But they cannot reject Greek culture because it's so powerful.\N{\rChinese}但他们能否能去掉希腓文化因为它很强大。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.28,1:00:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So, you know. Okay. So,\N{\rChinese}好吧！……??
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.24,1:00:30.82,English,,0,0,0,,this lecture is not about what happens in reality.\N{\rChinese}这场讲座不在说…
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.16,1:00:35.00,English,,0,0,0,,This lecture is about the new conception of\N{\rChinese}本次讲座关于罗马帝国所引入的全新现实观念。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.00,1:00:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,reality as introduced by the Roman Empire.\N{\rChinese}好的？但终究会成为全新现实。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.72,1:00:40.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But eventually, this will become the new reality.\N{\rChinese}Okay? But eventually, thiswill become the new reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.08,1:00:43.26,English,,0,0,0,,It will take time. Okay?\N{\rChinese}987. 需要时间。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.22,1:01:03.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, looking ahead.\N{\rChinese}987. 1?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.86,1:01:10.14,English,,0,0,0,,The Romans will introduce a new idea that\N{\rChinese}]\}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.14,1:01:14.04,English,,0,0,0,,will make piety and obedience the cornerstone of society.\N{\rChinese}将把虔诚与服从一一成为社会的基石。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.44,1:01:17.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This idea is called Christianity.\N{\rChinese}好的，回到此时刻！
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.14,1:01:21.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Looking ahead. Right?\N{\rChinese}“可”??
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.60,1:01:26.46,English,,0,0,0,,Like, this is not happening right now because\N{\rChinese}像，刚才那件事还没发生，因为罗马的概念还没到位。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.46,1:01:28.10,English,,0,0,0,,the Roman\N{\rChinese}罗马...??
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.10,1:01:33.82,English,,0,0,0,,conception is not as appealing as the Greek conception.\N{\rChinese}此时刻…
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.84,1:01:37.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But eventually, the Romans will create a new religion called Christianity\N{\rChinese}OK? 先后? 先后??
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.44,1:01:41.02,English,,0,0,0,,that will dominate and\N{\rChinese}OK? 先后?????
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.02,1:01:45.08,English,,0,0,0,,make piety the cornerstone of society\N{\rChinese}OK? ?????
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.08,1:01:46.80,English,,0,0,0,,and civilization.\N{\rChinese}和文明。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.14,1:01:48.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But looking ahead.\N{\rChinese}好的？接下来是...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.04,1:01:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions?\N{\rChinese}还有什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.96,1:02:02.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, next class.\N{\rChinese}好的。下一节课。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.60,1:02:05.62,English,,0,0,0,,We will. We will discuss Egypt.\N{\rChinese}我们会...
